                            <comment id="16905772" author="reta" created="Tue, 13 Aug 2019 03:18:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you for submitting the issue, indeed there is misalignment between server and client settings with respect to collection handling.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16909750" author="reta" created="Sat, 17 Aug 2019 15:37:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just to clarify this feature, which is CXF-specific in fact, as per &lt;a href=&quot;https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6570&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;RFC-6570: URI Template&lt;/a&gt; (&lt;a href=&quot;https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6570&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6570&lt;/a&gt;), the query parameters should be repeated to represent multiple values.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;   An explode modifier applied to a list variable causes the expansion
   to iterate over the list&apos;s member values.  For path and query
   parameter expansions, each member value is paired with the variable&apos;s
   name as a (varname, value) pair.  This allows path and query
   parameters to be repeated for multiple values, as in

     Given the variable assignments

       year  := (&quot;1965&quot;, &quot;2000&quot;, &quot;2012&quot;)
       dom   := (&quot;example&quot;, &quot;com&quot;)

     Example Template     Expansion

       find{?year*}       find?year=1965&amp;amp;year=2000&amp;amp;year=2012
       www{.dom*}         www.example.com
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16910153" author="sridharkumar" created="Mon, 19 Aug 2019 03:39:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=reta&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;reta&quot;&gt;reta&lt;/a&gt;&#160;Thanks for clarification and providing support to get Query Param in CSV format .&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-6941&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;CXF-6941&lt;/a&gt;, Sergy Beryozkin&#160; had mentioned that there is a possible performance hit. Do we still expect a Performance hit because of this change ?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16910875" author="reta" created="Tue, 20 Aug 2019 01:03:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=SridharKumar&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;SridharKumar&quot;&gt;SridharKumar&lt;/a&gt;, I believe the concerns which &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=sergey_beryozkin&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;sergey_beryozkin&quot;&gt;sergey_beryozkin&lt;/a&gt; had expressed are still apply for server-side, but in case of the client-side (this ticket) there should be no noticeable impact since there is no parsing happening but simple expansion. Potentially, could save some bandwidth for a large collections, the query string would be more compact, but the limits may still apply.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16914606" author="reta" created="Fri, 23 Aug 2019 20:30:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Documentation: &lt;a href=&quot;https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/CXF20DOC/JAX-RS+Advanced+Features#JAX-RSAdvancedFeatures-QueryStringCustomization&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/CXF20DOC/JAX-RS+Advanced+Features#JAX-RSAdvancedFeatures-QueryStringCustomization&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16917424" author="sridharkumar" created="Wed, 28 Aug 2019 05:21:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you much for the fix. &lt;br/&gt;
I don&apos;t see 3.2.11 label in the repository yet. Kindly let me know when the label will be created. Any tentative dates will be of great help.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/org/apache/cxf/cxf/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/org/apache/cxf/cxf/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16917550" author="coheigea" created="Wed, 28 Aug 2019 08:30:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We just released 3.2.10, so it&apos;ll likely be 6-8 weels before 3.2.11 is released.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16923047" author="sridharkumar" created="Thu, 5 Sep 2019 04:54:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry to come back on this again.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As per [3.2|&lt;a href=&quot;https://cxf.apache.org/docs/32-migration-guide.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://cxf.apache.org/docs/32-migration-guide.html&lt;/a&gt;] migration guide, 3.2 requires Java 8&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Some of our applications are still running on Java 7, using cxf 3.1.18&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Since the original csv support was added from 3.1.8, is it possible to retrofit the fix in 3.1.x ?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note: We are already in process of migrating to Java 8. Sorry for the trouble.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16923291" author="reta" created="Thu, 5 Sep 2019 11:08:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hey &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=SridharKumar&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;SridharKumar&quot;&gt;SridharKumar&lt;/a&gt; ,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Sure, no worries, I could port it to 3.1.x but we are not planning to have new releases in this line &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;, 3.1.8 was the last one.&lt;/p&gt;

